    <!-- 
    Chosen Palette: Lego Neutrals & Brights
    Application Structure Plan: A task-oriented, tab-based Single Page Application (SPA). The structure mirrors a user's journey: learning foundations, finding practical workshops, building a toolkit, and accessing external resources. This non-linear structure is chosen for maximum usability, allowing users to jump directly to the section that meets their immediate need (e.g., "I need a 10-minute icebreaker for 20 people"). Key interactions include dynamic filtering of workshops and an interactive chart for comparing Lego kits, making data consumption efficient and engaging.
    Visualization & Content Choices: 
    - Core Principles: Goal=Inform -> 4-column card grid (HTML/Tailwind) for scannability.
    - 4-Step Process: Goal=Organize -> Horizontal process flow diagram (HTML/Tailwind) to show sequence. Interaction: Click to expand details.
    - Workshop Blueprints: Goal=Compare/Organize -> Interactive filterable card library (JS/HTML/Tailwind). Interaction: Radio/button filters dynamically update the displayed workshop cards. This is the core user task.
    - Kit Comparison: Goal=Compare -> Interactive Bar Chart (Chart.js) for high-level visual comparison (Cost/Versatility), with clickable tabs below for detailed info. This is more engaging than a static table.
    - DIY Kit Lists: Goal=Inform -> Styled checklist format (HTML/Tailwind) for practical, actionable guidance.
    CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used.
    -->
