                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-2 text-slate-900">Building Your Toolkit</h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6 max-w-3xl">The right collection of bricks is crucial for a successful workshop. It's the "vocabulary" your participants will use to express their ideas. You can buy official kits or build your own more cost-effectively.</p>
                    
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-slate-800">Kit Comparison: Official vs. DIY</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-4 max-w-3xl">This chart provides a quick comparison of different kit options based on relative cost and versatility for various workshop types. Hover over the bars for details.</p>
                    <div class="chart-container">
                        <canvas id="kitChart"></canvas>
                    </div>

                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 mt-12 text-slate-800">DIY Kit Building Guide</h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6 max-w-3xl">Creating your own kit is often the most flexible and cost-effective approach. The goal is to create a "brick soup" with a wide variety of shapes, sizes, colors, and special pieces to spark metaphorical thinking. Here's a recommended shopping list to get started.</p>
                     <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-3 text-slate-700">Core Components</h4>
                            <ul class="space-y-3">
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="bg-blue-500 rounded-full w-5 h-5 text-white text-xs flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0">‚úì</span><span><span class="font-semibold">Basic Bricks:</span> Multiple Lego Classic boxes (e.g., 10698) for a wide color and size variety.</span></li>
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="bg-blue-500 rounded-full w-5 h-5 text-white text-xs flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0">‚úì</span><span><span class="font-semibold">Minifigures:</span> Crucial for representing people. Aim for 4-5 per participant. Buy People Packs or find bulk lots on eBay.</span></li>
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="bg-blue-500 rounded-full w-5 h-5 text-white text-xs flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0">‚úì</span><span><span class="font-semibold">DUPLO Bricks:</span> Include a selection. Their larger size is great for building foundations and representing big-picture concepts.</span></li>
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="bg-blue-500 rounded-full w-5 h-5 text-white text-xs flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0">‚úì</span><span><span class="font-semibold">Base Plates:</span> Small plates for individual models and a few large ones for shared "landscape" builds.</span></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-semibold text-lg mb-3 text-slate-700">Specialty Components</h4>
                             <ul class="space-y-3">
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="bg-green-500 rounded-full w-5 h-5 text-white text-xs flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0">‚úì</span><span><span class="font-semibold">Connectors:</span> Technic pieces, hinges, and joints for creating dynamic models and connections.</span></li>
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="bg-green-500 rounded-full w-5 h-5 text-white text-xs flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0">‚úì</span><span><span class="font-semibold">Figurative Elements:</span> Wheels, windows, fences, ladders, trees, and animals. These are metaphor gold.</span></li>
                                <li class="flex items-start"><span class="bg-green-500 rounded-full w-5 h-5 text-white text-xs flex items-center justify-center mr-3 mt-1 flex-shrink-0">‚úì</span><span><span class="font-semibold">Themed Sets (Your Own!):</span> Integrate your Star Wars & Harry Potter bricks! A lightsaber can represent a powerful tool; a magic wand, a special skill. These add fun and rich, pre-understood metaphors.</span></li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
